<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                    <head>No. 41.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                    Office</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-05"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 5,
                            1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herewith, for your information, a
                        copy of a letter which I have received from the United States minister in
                        London, pressing for the early trial of Mr. Patrick Slattery, a naturalized
                        citizen of the United States, who is imprisoned in Limerick County jail,
                        under the protection of person and property (Ireland) act, 1881.<note n="*" xml:id="d166fn1">No. 40.</note></p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>GRANVILLE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>